<br>
Rexx then goes on a bit about not having enough shawls prepared, blah blah blah.<br>
<br>
Rexx Frostweaver says 'Gather five strands of crystalline silk thread and combine them in a sewing kit to make a crystalline silk fiber. Take this container and combine a glowing shardworm bile with three of the fibers to form a piece of glowing crystalline silk. Five pieces of glowing crystalline silk sewn to your fur-lined shawl will yield a beautiful silk shawl. Become a master in the art of tailoring before risking all you've worked for and be sure to let me inspect your work when it's complete.'<br>
<br>
He then gives you a Vase-like container, 4-slot, which you can combine the items in.<br>
<br>
Crystaline Silk Thread will be found on the Spiders in Velketor's Laboratory, NOT on the Crystal Spiders under Crystal Caverns.  These threads are NO DROP.<br>
<br>
Yesterday, I wrote: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Drop rates per thread are said to be the same.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Boy, was I wrong.  After spending two hours in the Laboratory last night, with almost non-stop spider pulls (don't pull yet, I haven't medded eno... oh dear) we found ZERO threads.  To make matters worse, creatures here drop NO coin, and only a scattering of minor items (crystaline statues will drop Velium pieces and bricks, so you don't have to run all the way to CC, 1 in 5 spiders drops 1 stackable Cryst. Silk)  The spiders DO cast invisibility on themselves, and DO poison and backstab for nasty damage.  Also, grab someone who can Entangle on a pull, the spidesr run only slightly slower than a SOW cast by a 45 druid.  <br>
<br>
An entrance to Velketor's Laboratory can be found in the southwest corner of the Great Divide.  The Lab is also a up-down tower-like zone (you can see up about 6 levels), and Levitate is dispelled on entry and cannot be reapplied.  It is possible that the Thread only drops off of a specific Spider in the dungeon (like scrolls only drop from Guardian Shardwurms, not Ancient or Elder), I'm sure we just need to get more information from exploring groups.<br>
<br>
Best guess to date is Glowing Shardwurm Bile comes from the Shardwurm caves in the Great Divide.<br>
<br>
So, it'll take a minimum of 75 silk + 5 bile + ShawlLevel4.  And pray you don't fail that final sew.<br>
